<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 08 at 5:59PM CST  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...Strong storms with heavy rain will impact portions of northern
Rankin, east central Hinds and southeastern Madison Counties through
630 PM CST...
At 556 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking an area of storms with
heavy rain near Madison, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Fannin around 600 PM CST.
Goshen Springs and Pisgah around 605 PM CST.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
